bib_record.title: New Cross-Sections and intercomparison of deuteron monitor reactions on Al, Ti, Fe, Ni and Cu

free_txt: . Main Reference
Stacks contaning combinations of the
foils were irradiated in Faraday cup for 1 to 2 hours
with 32 to 65 nA deuteron beam. The Faraday cup
was equipped with long collimator and electron
supressor. The primary bombarding energy were 30 and
50 MeV. The results obtained for the reactions on the
Al foils also serve as internal monitors confirming
the beam current measurements. The six studied
reactions hence form a consistent database for
monitoring. That was comfirmed by critical evaluation
Of the available literature data.
Targets were high purity metal foils
Al 92.6 microns
Ti 12.1 microns
Fe 14.3 microns
Ni 15.5 microns
Cu 47.5 microns
Uncertainty of the incident deuteron energy
was estimated taking into account the cumulative
Effects of the Primary Uncertainty Sources
incident energy, foil thickness, beam straggling.
The possible energy shift of a representing point in
the excitation function ranges from +-0.3 upto
Total uncertainties of the cross section
values were calculated as root-mean-square of all
uncertainties added in quadrature.
The estimated uncertainties on the cross sections
were calculated taking into account
Beam current                  5-8%
Number of target nuclei       3%
Nuclear data                  3%
Detector efficiency           3-6%
Peak area                   1-5%
Correction for recoil effect was about 5%
